wav-play is a simple and lightweight console based WAVE file player.

Dependencies:
  Simple DirectMedia Layer 2 (SDL2) - https://www.libsdl.org/

Code Used:
  Joel Yliluoma â€” https://bisqwit.iki.fi/ (https://github.com/bisqwit/speech_synth_series/blob/master/ep2-pcmaudio/pcmaudio-tiny2.cc)


Building/Usage:
  To build wavplay run make in the root directory. In order to use
  wavplay you must run "./wavplay <your wav file>".

Testing:
  1."./wavplay Test_Outlier_Audio.wav"
  2."./wavplay Greek_National_Anthem.wav"

Known Bugs:
  Once a file starts to play it cannot be stopped via a keyboard interrupt or by SIGTERM and can only be killed with a SIGKILL signal.
